observations.recommendation:
We commended the LGU’s efforts to locate the necessary documents for completed infrastructure projects from CYs 2016 to 2019 to facilitate their proper recognition in the books of accounts.

On the other hand, we recommended the following to Management:

a. The Municipal Accountant, General Services Officer and Municipal Engineer collaborate in locating documents and information pertaining to the road networks of the LGU for CY 2015 and prior years to properly recognize the same in the LGU’s Financial Statements for a fair presentation of the PPE account;

b. The Municipal Accountant to trace the expenditures for road networks in CYs 2016-2018 that were recorded in various PPE accounts and to reclassify thereof in the Road Networks account;

c. The Municipal Engineer provide the Municipal Accountant with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects already recognized in the books of the agency;

d. The General Services Officer maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and shall keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components;

e. The Municipal Accountant prepare the Journal Voucher to record the inventory of the local road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local Road Network Ledger Card;

f. The Municipal Accountant keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network, and ensure that these are 100 percent booked-up in 2019 and thereafter consistent with COA Circular No. 2015-008; and

g. The Municipal Accountant comply with complete disclosure of road networks in the Notes to the Financial Statements of the LGU.

We recommended the Management to direct the following concerned officials:

The Municipal Accountant to perform a detailed reconciliation of records of the cash accounts and draw adjusting/correcting entries as necessary;

The Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to periodically reconcile their records;

The Municipal Treasurer to request for the closure of the dormant bank account under the General Fund;

The Municipal Accountant to maintain an updated and accurate subsidiary records for each bank accounts. Thereafter, posting of transactions affecting the cash accounts must be made real time; and

The Municipal Accountant to submit the Bank Reconciliation Statements timely as prescribed.

