Require the Accountable Officers concerned to immediately liquidate their outstanding cash advances pursuant to the provisions of PD 1445 and COA Circular No. 97-002, otherwise, appropriate charges may be filed against them for failure to settle their cash advances, if warranted;
Comply with the aforementioned letter of COA, anent the request for write-off made by the LGU, issued on January 30, 2023 for the lacking supporting documents; and
Not to grant additional cash advance to concerned officials and employees unless the previous cash advance granted to them have been liquidated.

The Inventory Committee conduct actual count of the remaining balance of purchased Inventories and reconcile the report to the Accounting Office for adjustment;
Require the Inventory Committee to submit the RPCI and henceforth prepare and submit yearly to the Auditor a duly certified and approved RPCI not later than January 31 of each year;
The General Services Officer identify the issuances made for Inventories and prepare the necessary document needed for the recognition of related expense to be submitted to the Office of the Municipal Accountant; and
The Municipal Accountant prepare the necessary adjusting entry, if there’s any, to reflect the actual balance of Inventories as at December 31, 2024 for fair presentation of the financial statements.

