We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor including all those concerned strictly follow the guidelines in the utilization of LGU share from tobacco excise tax.  The responsibility in screening qualified beneficiaries lodged with the LGU management thus, the following documents be submitted:  

Memorandum of Agreement with the concerned beneficiaries; 

Feasibility study or project proposals on how they account and operate/manage the funds from the Tobacco Excise Tax;

Utilization report based on the project study in order to account properly all the funds released; and 

Proof that these beneficiaries are tobacco farmers producing native burley tobacco products pursuant to RA 8240 and Joint Circular No. 2009-1 dated November 3, 2009.

We also have recommended that management exercise prudence in the discharge of fiscal responsibility to avoid wastage of government resources and enhance monitoring and supervision over the projects, if there’s any.
